overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too
  generic. The agent embarked on a comprehensive design update, starting with a
  new sleep-themed color palette and custom utility classes. This was followed
  by a redesign of the main questionnaire form layout, including a more engaging
  progress indicator and subtle background elements. The introductory section
  was transformed with a hero component and feature cards, and all core UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders received a polished,
  consistent look. A critical bug related to  values being passed to input
  fields was also identified and fixed. After initial implementation, user
  feedback highlighted remaining inconsistencies in the report section's card
  headers and text colors, which were subsequently addressed to ensure a fully
  cohesive and calming visual experience throughout the application.
